oc:kn_3b316059 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculating sample size for a specific test" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use site-wide average conversion rates for sample size calculations; use the specific page and metric under test." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Wrong baseline rate leads to dramatically incorrect sample size estimates, either underpowered or wasteful" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_5efaa98a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before launching any A/B test" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before running a test, verify: daily traffic to page, baseline conversion rate for that specific page, and the minimum lift worth detecting (MDE). Calculate days = (sample per variant × variants) / (daily traffic × % exposed)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Running a test without feasibility assessment wastes time and resources if it cannot reach significance" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_6eb3e5f9 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When test duration exceeds 4 weeks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid running tests longer than 4-8 weeks due to novelty effects wearing off, external factors, and opportunity cost of other tests." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Extended test duration introduces confounding variables and blocks the testing pipeline" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ae3d6d92 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When calculated test duration exceeds feasible limits" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When sample requirements are too high: increase MDE (accept detecting only larger effects), reduce variants, combine traffic across pages, test upstream in funnel, or fall back to qualitative decisions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Not every page has enough traffic for statistical testing; alternative approaches still yield actionable insights" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b202a847 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing A/B/n tests with more than 2 variants" ;
    oc:directiveContent "With 3+ variants, apply ~1.5x multiplier for 3 variants, ~2x for 4 variants, or use Bonferroni correction to account for multiple comparisons." ;
    oc:hasRationale "More comparisons increase false positive rate; without correction, statistical validity is compromised" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b4048a5d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning segmented analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If you plan to analyze segments post-test, calculate sample size for the smallest segment you care about, not total traffic." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A test powered for overall traffic will be underpowered for any individual segment" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b6bd3d5b a oc:FallbackStrategy,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When you need to check results before reaching full sample size" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For high-risk changes requiring early stopping, use sequential testing methods (Optimizely Stats Accelerator, VWO SmartStats, PostHog Bayesian) instead of fixed-horizon tests." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Sequential testing adjusts for multiple looks at the data, preserving statistical validity while allowing early stopping" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_bb016b8b a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining minimum test duration" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Run tests for at least 1 full week to capture day-of-week variation, 2 business cycles for B2B, and through paydays for e-commerce." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Day-of-week and cyclical behavioral patterns create conversion variance that invalidates short tests" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

